  "description": "<i>Checkmate</i> is a chess program with basic features: it does not only allow a game against the computer, but also player vs. player and computer vs. computer.<br><br>The board itself is drawn in 2D, the window on the left is showing the moves in the game in standard chess notation, while on the right a windows is displaying the computers analysis and progress.<br><br>Games can be replayed and saved. Some analysis functions help the player. An option allows to create a board position from scratch and play from that position. A small opening library is delivered with the program and can be modified.<br><br>The difficulty can be adjusted, basically by the time per move (10 seconds up to 10 minutes per move).",
